20200124 at Heaven's gate

January 24,2020.

New Year's Eve, the 30th day of the 12th lunar month.

The second day of the city closure in Wuhan.

The first day the gates of Heaven were sealed.

In the afternoon on his way back from his visit to his father's grave, he received a notice of the closing of the gate of Heaven in the group. At this point, Wuhan 8 + 1 City Circle all fall.

We put on our masks, went out carefully, and drove slowly. The rainy street, already deserted. Came to the cemetery, was told: received notice, not allowed to enter immediately. Uncle held an umbrella, to father for food and wine, with a towel to wipe the tombstone, burning paper money. WE TAKE TURNS TO WORSHIP INCENSE, chanting: Father, the New Year, eat well... Dad was still the same, looking at US and grinning.

New Year's Eve dinner. Still. Only without daddy's pickles. I lost my vacation. Sissy trapped in Wuhan. The one and only, as if I were to give my father's mother-in-law the gift of silence. I think of how many families can not be reunited, this New Year's Eve, I am very satisfied.

In fact, a lot of words, but still can only remember water. The body is in the infected area, the heart is experiencing, can not escape. We'll just have to get through it, and then we'll regurgitate it. Heather sends her condolences: Is there anything you need? Is there food or drink? Is there a cat? Here's a unified response: don't worry, eat and drink, have a net and a dog, just don't go out to surf!

In addition to the old year, I wish you: Wash your hands! MORE VENTILATION! Masks on! KEEP SAFE!
